        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Office of Ezekiel &#38; Co.<lb/>
                Acution and Commission Merchangs&#44;<lb/>
                Nos. 19 &#38; 21 West Pearl Street<lb/></p>
            <p>Cincinnati&#44; Eve Pesach 5537.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais.<lb/>
                My valued Friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>How truly pleased was I to<lb/> <sic>recieve</sic> a few lines from you&#44; breathing<lb/> such true heartfelt sentiments.  I can only<lb/> use your own good feelings expressed to&#45;<lb/>wards me and mine&#44; to reciprocate again<lb/> in return&#44; to you and your dear family.<lb/>  May God bless you with health and long<lb/> life&#44; that you may enjoy for many years<lb/> the anniversary of our nations freedom&#44;<lb/> surrounded by all your dear ones.<lb/></p>
            <p>I hope this may meet you&#44; dear Nina&#44; and<lb/> all the rest of your family well&#44; all our<lb/> dear ones unite with me in love to you<lb/> and all.  I saw Mr Kramer on his re&#45;<lb/>turn yesterday&#44; he told me that <sic>if</sic> af&#45;<lb/>forded him much pleasure to meet you<lb/> and dear Nina.  I trust <hi rend="underline">you</hi> were pleased<lb/> with him&#44; he is an estimable young man<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of high moral and <sic>intelectual</sic> culture&#44;<lb/> and I suppose you have <sic>percieved</sic> his<lb/> earnestness in our college scheme&#44;<lb/> he told me that you told him your cong&#45;<lb/>regation were not financially circumstan&#45;<lb/>ced to unite with us.  I am in hopes that<lb/> the bona&#45;fide members will&#44; when properly<lb/> appealed to&#44; consent <hi rend="underline">to tax themselves</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">the small sum of 25 cts quarterly</hi>&#44; to be<lb/> added to their bills for Educational purpo&#45;<lb/>ses.  I think were you to see Mr Sultzberger&#44;<lb/> Henry Cohen and one or two others&#44; that it<lb/> may be arranged so that our old cong&#45;<lb/>regation may be represented&#44; the money<lb/> need only be paid in such <sic>instalments</sic> as<lb/> convenient.  I shall write to Mr S. concern&#45;<lb/>ing it.  It is pleasing to see how New York<lb/> has been stimulated recently&#44; more the mer&#45;<lb/>rier.  We want primary schools&#44; as I have<lb/> always told you&#44; you will find that Dr W.<lb/> is all right in Judaism&#44; it will not suffer by<lb/> any act of his you may depend.  I will de&#45;<lb/>liver your kind words to him and dear Hannah.<lb/></p>
            <p>Accept my best wishes&#44; with love to dear<lb/> Nina.  I am as Ever truly yrs<lb/>
                						Jacob Ezekiel<lb/></p>
                <p>Excuse brevity.<lb/></p>
        </body>
